# API controllers (LifeInsuranceCRM.API)

## Role

Controllers translate HTTP to use case calls and map `ProcessResponse<T>` to `IActionResult`. **No business logic** (validation that belongs in Core, authorization decisions beyond attributes, orchestration).

## Conventions

- Prefer `[ApiController]` and explicit `[Route("api/…")]` (kebab or resource style; keep routes consistent within the project).
- Controllers inherit **`ApiControllerBase`** and inject **`IProcessResponseActionMapper`** (via base constructor).
- Inject the use case with **`[FromServices] I…UseCase`** on the action unless the controller already holds a single injected dependency for all actions.
- Include **`CancellationToken cancellationToken`** on actions; build **`ProcessRequest<T>`** via **`IProcessRequestFactory.Create(payload, cancellationToken)`**.
- Return **`FromUseCase(useCase.Execute(processRequest))`**; pass a success lambda only for `CreatedAtAction` / `NoContent` responses.
- Success: branch on `ProcessResponse.Status`, not null `Result`.
- **`GlobalUsings`**: import `LifeInsuranceCRM.API.Services` as needed.

## Auth

Use `[Authorize]`, `[AllowAnonymous]`, and policy attributes as appropriate. Do not re-implement JWT parsing in the controller; Core uses `IActorTracker` after auth middleware/filters run.
